result.execSummary:
The defendant Tina Lee Davis was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Tina Lee Davis in court with attorney Joel Alan Mogren.  Margaret Anne Kunisch appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy court clerk cmt.
Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by parties. 

Defendant ordered to serve 3 months in the House of Correction with credit of 3 days time served.  Court STAYED the sentence and placed the defendant on probation for 12 months with the following conditions:

- Anger management course. 
- Pay all costs, fees and surcharges during term of probation.  Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment.

Defendant Tina Lee Davis in court with attorney Joel Alan Mogren.  Margaret Anne Kunisch appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy court clerk cmt.
Defendant prepared to enter change of plea.  Hearing proceeded.  Negotiations set forth by the state.

Defendant changes his plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty.   Defendant advised that if not a United States Citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights.  Guilty Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.  Defendant shall provide a DNA sample for the Data Bank and pay all appropriate costs.  Court ordered case adjourned for sentencing in Branch 45.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for January 13, 2016 at 08:30 am.
